卵母細胞與胚之細胞週期調控
利用不同CDK轉磷酸酵素抑制劑（cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor）如 
          roscovitine, indirubin,BLⅠ，探討其抑制豬卵母細胞原泡核崩解之效果，以利原泡核轉置（GV transfer）之研究，並於後續試驗將進行藥物移除後，評估卵母細胞發育之能力。


圖一 Inhibition of 
            germinal vesicle breakdown (GVBD) of pig oocytes treated with different 
            concentrations of roscovitine during in vitro maturation.




圖二 Control of cell cycle stages 
            in rabbit fetal and Taiwan black bear fibroblasts without chemical treatment. Cycling cells 
            were cultured in DMEM supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum. When 
            cells (A) were grown to 60-70% confluence and serum starvation was 
            performed for 1 to 5 days, in which serum was reduced to 0.5% in DMEM 
            medium. (B) Fetal fibroblasts were proliferated to 80-100% confluence 
            in the culture dish when the effect of contact inhibition of the cultured 
            cells was maximized.(C)Taiwan black bear fibroblasts
　


 圖三 Representative proportions of cycling 
              fibroblasts correspondence to the cell cycle stages after the fluorescence-activated 
              cell scan (FACs) determination. Propidium iodide (PI) was used for 
			detection of DNA content. G0/G1: gap phase, S: DNA synthesis phase, 
			G2/M: G2/Metaphase transition
 　






